                            <comment id="27970" author="adilger" created="Mon, 6 Feb 2012 13:11:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing this as a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-797&quot; title=&quot;Test failure on test suite ost-pools, subtest test_14, test_18, test_23&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-797&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-797&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which already landed to master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="26819" author="pjones" created="Wed, 18 Jan 2012 13:44:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think that it makes sense to create a TT ticket about the insufficient information on this report so that we can get that problem fixed and there is sufficient information to diagnose the problem if it reoccurs in the future.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Chris has asked for tickets to be opened whenever we encounter situations where we have insufficient information to debug a reported test failure.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Please get them to create  ticket, please ask that they clearly describe what information was required, and how it is generated by Lustre/Linux.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="26685" author="hongchao.zhang" created="Mon, 16 Jan 2012 22:23:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;the debug info isn&apos;t enough to get the reason of the issue (there is only a little test&amp;amp;console output in maloo!), &lt;br/&gt;
can we get the debug log to see what happened during the long time(3600s)?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
